description: Unique Carrier Code. When the same code has been used by multiple carriers, a numeric suffix is used for earlier users, for example, PA, PA(1), PA(2). Use this field for analysis across a range of years.
name: UNIQUE_CARRIER

description: An identification number assigned by US DOT to identify a unique airline (carrier). A unique airline (carrier) is defined as one holding and reporting under the same DOT certificate regardless of its Code, Name, or holding company/corporation.
name: AIRLINE_ID

description: Code assigned by IATA and commonly used to identify a carrier. As the same code may have been assigned to different carriers over time, the code is not always unique. For analysis, use the Unique Carrier Code.
name: CARRIER

description: Origin Airport, Airport ID. An identification number assigned by US DOT to identify a unique airport.  Use this field for airport analysis across a range of years because an airport can change its airport code and airport codes can be reused.
name: ORIGIN_AIRPORT_ID

description: Origin Airport, Airport Sequence ID. An identification number assigned by US DOT to identify a unique airport at a given point of time.  Airport attributes, such as airport name or coordinates, may change over time.
name: ORIGIN_AIRPORT_SEQ_ID

description: Origin Airport, City Market ID. City Market ID is an identification number assigned by US DOT to identify a city market.  Use this field to consolidate airports serving the same city market.
name: ORIGIN_CITY_MARKET_ID

description: Destination Airport, Airport ID. An identification number assigned by US DOT to identify a unique airport.  Use this field for airport analysis across a range of years because an airport can change its airport code and airport codes can be reused.
name: DEST_AIRPORT_ID

description: Destination Airport, Airport Sequence ID. An identification number assigned by US DOT to identify a unique airport at a given point of time.  Airport attributes, such as airport name or coordinates, may change over time.
name: DEST_AIRPORT_SEQ_ID

description: Destination Airport, City Market ID. City Market ID is an identification number assigned by US DOT to identify a city market.  Use this field to consolidate airports serving the same city market.
name: DEST_CITY_MARKET_ID

description: Difference in minutes between scheduled and actual departure time. Early departures show negative numbers.
name: DEP_DELAY

description: Difference in minutes between scheduled and actual departure time. Early departures set to 0.
name: DEP_DELAY_NEW

description: Departure Delay Indicator, 15 Minutes or More (1=Yes)
name: DEP_DEL15

description: Departure Delay intervals, every (15 minutes from <-15 to >180)
name: DEP_DELAY_GROUP

description: CRS Departure Time Block, Hourly Intervals
name: DEP_TIME_BLK

description: Difference in minutes between scheduled and actual arrival time. Early arrivals show negative numbers.
name: ARR_DELAY

description: Difference in minutes between scheduled and actual arrival time. Early arrivals set to 0.
name: ARR_DELAY_NEW

description: Arrival Delay Indicator, 15 Minutes or More (1=Yes)
name: ARR_DEL15

description: Arrival Delay intervals, every (15-minutes from <-15 to >180)
name: ARR_DELAY_GROUP

description: CRS Arrival Time Block, Hourly Intervals
name: ARR_TIME_BLK

description: CRS Elapsed Time of Flight, in Minutes
name: CRS_ELAPSED_TIME

description: Elapsed Time of Flight, in Minutes
name: ACTUAL_ELAPSED_TIME

description: Distance Intervals, every 250 Miles, for Flight Segment
name: DISTANCE_GROUP
